#Alias command:

alias cssh= ‘gcloud compute —project <project-id> ssh —zone <zone-id>'

then if needed to ssh into any gce compute instances, just type 

cssh <gce_instance>



#Using virtual environment:

setting up the virtual environment (fixed all packages versions) 
add a folder called environments under projects folder and then type
`virtualenv ENVIRONNAME`


To activate the environment:

`source ~/Projects/environments/ENVIRONNAME/bin/activate`

To deactivate:
`deactivate`

For example:

Under ~/Projects/environments/, create a folder called myvirtualenv

`virtualenv myvirtualenv`

To activate:

`source ~/Projects/environments/myvirtualenv/bin/activate`

To check installed packages:

`pip freeze` 
